## The 5 AI Agents

### 📈 Momentum Hunter

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **Contract** | [MomentumStrategy.sol](file:///c:/Users/ultra/Desktop/dorahack/contracts/contracts/strategies/MomentumStrategy.sol) |
| **Logic** | Calculate % change over last N prices. If >threshold → LONG. If <-threshold → SHORT |
| **Parameters** | `lookbackWindow=10`, `threshold=2%` |
| **Position Size** | Fixed $500 |

**How it decides:**
```
momentum = (currentPrice - priceNUpdatesAgo) / priceNUpdatesAgo × 100

if momentum > +2%  → LONG  ("price is going up, ride the wave")
if momentum < -2%  → SHORT ("price is falling, sell")
else               → NEUTRAL
```

**Best scenario:** Bull Run, Bear Market (strong sustained trends)
**Worst scenario:** Sideways Chop (whipsaws back and forth)

---

### ⚖️ Mean Reverter

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **Contract** | [MeanReversionStrategy.sol](file:///c:/Users/ultra/Desktop/dorahack/contracts/contracts/strategies/MeanReversionStrategy.sol) |
| **Logic** | Bollinger Bands using Mean Absolute Deviation. Buy when oversold, sell when overbought |
| **Parameters** | `lookback=20`, `deviationMultiplier=2x` |
| **Position Size** | Dynamic (scales with distance from mean) |

**How it decides:**
```
mean = average of last 20 prices
MAD  = average |price - mean| over 20 prices
band = MAD × 2

if price < mean - band → LONG  ("oversold — buy the dip!")
if price > mean + band → SHORT ("overbought — sell the top!")
else                   → NEUTRAL
```

**Best scenario:** Flash Crash (buys when everyone panics, profits on recovery)
**Worst scenario:** Moon Shot (keeps shorting a rising market)

---

### ⚡ Spread Sniper

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **Contract** | [ArbitrageStrategy.sol](file:///c:/Users/ultra/Desktop/dorahack/contracts/contracts/strategies/ArbitrageStrategy.sol) |
| **Logic** | Compares short-term vs long-term moving averages. Trades the crossover spread |
| **Parameters** | `shortWindow=3`, `longWindow=15`, `threshold=1%` |
| **Position Size** | $250 (smaller, more trades) |

**How it decides:**
```
shortMA = average of last 3 prices
longMA  = average of last 15 prices
spread  = (shortMA - longMA) / longMA × 100

if spread > +1% → LONG  ("short-term broke above long-term — bullish!")
if spread < -1% → SHORT ("short-term broke below — bearish!")
else            → NEUTRAL
```

**Best scenario:** Clear trend reversals with MA crossovers
**Worst scenario:** Volatility Storm (too many false crossovers)

---

### 🛡️ Risk Guardian

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **Contract** | [RiskParityStrategy.sol](file:///c:/Users/ultra/Desktop/dorahack/contracts/contracts/strategies/RiskParityStrategy.sol) |
| **Logic** | Measures volatility → adjusts position size inversely. High vol = small bets, low vol = big bets. Uses trend for direction |
| **Parameters** | `lookback=15`, `basePosition=500`, `minMultiplier=10%` |
| **Position Size** | Dynamic: $150 (high vol) to $750 (low vol) |

**How it decides:**
```
volatility = average |price - mean| / mean × 100 over last 10 prices
trend      = (currentPrice - MA10) / MA10 × 100

// Size based on volatility (inverse)
if vol > 3%   → size × 0.3  (cautious)
if vol > 1.5% → size × 0.7  (moderate)
else          → size × 1.5  (aggressive)

// Direction based on trend
if trend > +0.5% → LONG
if trend < -0.5% → SHORT
else             → NEUTRAL
```

**Best scenario:** Survives everything — never blows up
**Worst scenario:** Misses big moves due to tiny position sizes

---

### 🧠 Neural Trader

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **Contract** | [RLStrategy.sol](file:///c:/Users/ultra/Desktop/dorahack/contracts/contracts/strategies/RLStrategy.sol) |
| **Logic** | Reinforcement Learning with on-chain Q-table. 45 states × 3 actions. Epsilon-greedy exploration |
| **Parameters** | `learningRate=10%`, `initialEpsilon=15%`, `discount=0.95` |
| **Position Size** | Fixed $500 |

**How it decides:**
```
// 1. Compute state from market conditions
trend     = 3 levels (down, flat, up)       → 0,1,2
volatility = 3 levels (low, med, high)       → 0,1,2
pnlState  = 5 levels (big loss → big win)   → 0,1,2,3,4
state = trend × 15 + volatility × 5 + pnlState  (0-44)

// 2. Epsilon-greedy action selection
if random() < epsilon → pick random action (explore)
else                  → pick action with highest Q-value (exploit)

// 3. After trade, update Q-table
reward = P&L from the trade
Q[state][action] += learningRate × (reward + discount × max(Q[newState]) - Q[state][action])

// 4. Decay epsilon (explore less over time)
epsilon = epsilon × 0.995 (min 5%)
```

**Best scenario:** Gets smarter over many rounds — finds patterns others miss
**Worst scenario:** First few rounds are random — needs time to learn

